      "content": "i get the official line on telemetry, but it feels like a deflection. if you look at the specific packet intervals, they don't match standard diagnostic bursts. they look more like they're trying to sync with a biological frequency or something. if a company wanted to harvest massive amounts of psychological data or \"patterns\" from a whole population, wouldn't using the most ubiquitous OS in the world under the guise of a \"security update\" be the perfect way to do it? it just seems too easy for them to hide it in plain sight.",
