      "content": "i'm not just talking about \"hypothetical scenarios\" though. if you actually examine the way modern telemetry pushes massive datasets through encrypted tunnels that bypass standard user-facing firewalls, it looks less like \"improving service\" and more like creating a massive, unmonitored stream of behavioral metadata. if someone wanted to map out the collective cognitive state of a population, wouldn't they use the exact same infrastructure that's already built into every office and home on the planet? it's not sci-fi if the infrastructure is already there. don't you think a tech giant would have the capability to mask a data-gathering operation inside a mandatory system patch?",
